<paragraph id="AF5BBB7D0D14FFD2A4B3FCFDD990A25E" blockId="1.[151,1436,845,1954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">
Annual herb, to 
<quantity id="681C16980D14FFD2A547FCFDD9C3A429" box="[355,431,845,871]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="cm" value="40.0">40 cm</quantity>
tall. Stem terete, unbranched or rarely branched, straight, erect, striate on lower portion, adpressed whitish tomentose with long hairs. Leaves 4–6-verticellate, sessile; blades elliptic-linear, 
<quantity id="681C16980D14FFD2A4B3FC2AD886A4FD" box="[151,234,922,948]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="cm" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3 cm</quantity>
× 
<quantity id="681C16980D14FFD2A52EFC2AD903A4FA" box="[266,367,922,948]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="3.0">3–7 mm</quantity>
, apex obtuse, margin not revolute, sometimes dentate apically, base rounded or broadly cuneate, tomentose on both surfaces, hairs unicellular, midrib elevated abaxially, lateral veins 3–5 on each side of midrib. Inflorescence terminal, 
<quantity id="681C16980D14FFD2A645FC58DAD4A34C" box="[609,696,1000,1026]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="cm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7 cm</quantity>
× 
<quantity id="681C16980D14FFD2A6F2FC58DB40A34C" box="[726,812,1000,1026]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="38.0">38 mm</quantity>
, densely flowered, not interrupted, tomentose; bracts linear, villose, longer than the calyx, long-hairy; calyx campanulate, 
<quantity id="681C16980D14FFD2A79DFBBEDC29A366" box="[953,1093,1038,1064]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="1.65" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.5">1.5–1.8 mm</quantity>
in length, 4-angled and more or less quadrangular, villose outside, lobes 5, subequal; corolla pinkish, very shortly exserted from the calyx tube, lobes oblong, subequal, pubescent outside, corolla tube about 
<quantity id="681C16980D14FFD2A789FBECDB9CA338" box="[941,1008,1116,1142]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
in length; stamens 4, about 
<quantity id="681C16980D14FFD2A11EFBECDD11A338" box="[1338,1405,1116,1142]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
in length, inserted at the mid-part of the corolla tube; filament twice as long as the corolla, joined to the middle of the corolla tube, hairy; anther stalks tapered at the base which is pubescent, bearded at the mid part and more than twice as long as the corolla; anther 1-locular, cell apex dehiscent. Ovary glabrous; stigma shortly bifid at apex. Nutlets not seen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E7FEE8F60D14FFD2A4E2FAADDB72A210" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="AF5BBB7D0D14FFD2A4E2FAADDB72A210" blockId="1.[151,1436,845,1954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A4E2FAADDA7DA279" bold="true" box="[198,529,1309,1335]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="68E4C0FE0D14FFD2A60BFAADDB5CA278" authorityName="Doan ex Gang Yao, Y. F. Deng &amp; X. J. Ge" authorityYear="2013" box="[559,816,1309,1334]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petelotii">
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A60BFAADDB5CA278" box="[559,816,1309,1334]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Pogostemon petelotii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in 
<collectingCountry id="D7F3FBED0D14FFD2A7FBFAADDC2BA279" box="[991,1095,1309,1335]" name="Thailand" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Thailand</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="D7F3FBED0D14FFD2A0B5FAADDC94A279" box="[1169,1272,1309,1335]" name="Vietnam" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
. It grows in grassland in open places at elevations of 
<quantity id="681C16980D14FFD2A652FAF4DB76A210" box="[630,794,1348,1374]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" unit="m" value="1150.0" valueMax="1300.0" valueMin="1000.0">1000–1300 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E7FEE8F60D14FFD2A4E2FADADD09A2E5" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="AF5BBB7D0D14FFD2A4E2FADADD09A2E5" blockId="1.[151,1436,845,1954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A4E2FADAD93BA2CA" bold="true" box="[198,343,1386,1412]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName id="68E4C0FE0D14FFD2A657FADBDABFA2CA" authorityName="Doan ex Gang Yao, Y. F. Deng &amp; X. J. Ge" authorityYear="2013" box="[627,723,1387,1412]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petelotii">
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A657FADBDABFA2CA" box="[627,723,1387,1412]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">petelotii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” was originally proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="CB75C68C0D14FFD2A017FADADCA4A2CA" author="Doan, T." box="[1075,1224,1386,1412]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" pagination="915 - 1046" refId="ref2510" refString="Doan, T. (1936) Labiatae. In: Lecomte, H. (ed.) Flore Generale de L'Indo - Chine 4. Masson, Paris, pp. 915 - 1046." type="book chapter" year="1936">Doan (1936)</bibRefCitation>
for the species to be in honor of French botanist P. A. Pételot (1885–after 1940), who first collected the species in 
<collectingCountry id="D7F3FBED0D14FFD2A0DEFA21DD0DA2E5" box="[1274,1377,1425,1451]" name="Vietnam" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E7FEE8F60D14FFD2A4E2FA07DD00A0EC" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="AF5BBB7D0D14FFD2A4E2FA07DCEBA1F4" blockId="1.[151,1436,845,1954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A4E2FA07D938A29F" bold="true" box="[198,340,1463,1489]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Discussion:</emphasis>
—According to the classification of 
<bibRefCitation id="CB75C68C0D14FFD2A6DAFA08DC5AA29C" author="Bhatti, G. R. &amp; Ingrouille, M." box="[766,1078,1464,1490]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" pagination="77 - 147" refId="ref2327" refString="Bhatti, G. R. &amp; Ingrouille, M. (1997) Systematics of Pogostemon (Labiatae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum, Botany Series 27: 77 - 147." type="book chapter" year="1997">Bhatti &amp; Ingrouille (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="68E4C0FE0D14FFD2A066FA08DD56A29F" authorityName="Doan ex Gang Yao, Y. F. Deng &amp; X. J. Ge" authorityYear="2013" box="[1090,1338,1464,1489]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petelotii">
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A066FA08DD56A29F" box="[1090,1338,1464,1489]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Pogostemon petelotii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A492FA6FD8A0A2B6" box="[182,204,1503,1528]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">P.</emphasis>
subgen. 
<taxonomicName id="68E4C0FE0D14FFD2A512FA6FD9D0A2B6" authority="" authorityName="Bhatti &amp; Ingrouille" authorityYear="1997" baseAuthorityName="Blume" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[310,444,1503,1528]" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Dysophylla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A512FA6FD9D0A2B6" box="[310,444,1503,1528]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Dysophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Obviously, it is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="68E4C0FE0D14FFD2A77DFA6FDB88A2B6" authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Bentham" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[857,996,1503,1528]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cruciatus">
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A77DFA6FDB88A2B6" box="[857,996,1503,1528]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">P. cruciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter by having the stems and leaves whitish adpressed tomentose (
<figureCitation id="37DFA7F80D14FFD2A72FF9B5DB1FA151" box="[779,883,1541,1567]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,246,1862,1883]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-86@2.[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A. Holotype of Pogostemon petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); B. Isotype of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K); C. Leaves of P. petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); D. Leaves of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K). Scale bars: C, D = 1 cm. A and C reproduced with permisson by the Muséum National d'Histoire Naturelle (MNHN), Paris; B and D with permission by Herbarium of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew (K))" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071557/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Fig. 1 C</figureCitation>
), leaf margins rarely revolute and sometimes dentate apically, midrib elevated conspicuously (
<figureCitation id="37DFA7F80D14FFD2A6F1F99CDB70A108" box="[725,796,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,245,1931,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,462,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-196@4.[151,1436,462,1915]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Trichome morphology of leaves under scanning electron microscope and light microscope. Pogostemon cruciatus (G. Forrest 25140, IBSC): A. Trichome on the upper surface; C. Trichome on the lower surface; E. 2–3-cellular trichome. P. petelotii (T. Sörensen et al. 6313, KUN): B. Trichome on the upper surface; D. Trichome on lower surface; F. unicellular trichome. Scale bars: E–F = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071563/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) and lateral veins in 3–5 pairs (
<figureCitation id="37DFA7F80D14FFD2A0B4F99CDC99A108" box="[1168,1269,1580,1606]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,246,1862,1883]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-86@2.[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A. Holotype of Pogostemon petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); B. Isotype of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K); C. Leaves of P. petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); D. Leaves of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K). Scale bars: C, D = 1 cm. A and C reproduced with permisson by the Muséum National d'Histoire Naturelle (MNHN), Paris; B and D with permission by Herbarium of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew (K))" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071557/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Fig. 1 C</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="68E4C0FE0D14FFD2A12FF99CD96BA122" authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Bentham" baseAuthorityYear="1830" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cruciatus">
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A12FF99CD96BA122" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Pogostemon cruciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the stems and leaves brown spreadingly hirsute (
<figureCitation id="37DFA7F80D14FFD2A7B5F9E2DB97A122" box="[913,1019,1618,1644]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,246,1862,1883]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-86@2.[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A. Holotype of Pogostemon petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); B. Isotype of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K); C. Leaves of P. petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); D. Leaves of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K). Scale bars: C, D = 1 cm. A and C reproduced with permisson by the Muséum National d'Histoire Naturelle (MNHN), Paris; B and D with permission by Herbarium of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew (K))" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071557/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Fig. 1 D</figureCitation>
), leaf margin usually revolute and quite entire, midrib inconspicuously elevated (
<figureCitation id="37DFA7F80D14FFD2A69BF9C9DB48A1DD" box="[703,804,1657,1683]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,246,1862,1883]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-86@2.[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A. Holotype of Pogostemon petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); B. Isotype of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K); C. Leaves of P. petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); D. Leaves of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K). Scale bars: C, D = 1 cm. A and C reproduced with permisson by the Muséum National d'Histoire Naturelle (MNHN), Paris; B and D with permission by Herbarium of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew (K))" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071557/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Fig. 1 D</figureCitation>
) and lateral veins invisible (
<figureCitation id="37DFA7F80D14FFD2A052F9C9DCB3A1DD" box="[1142,1247,1657,1683]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,246,1862,1883]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-86@2.[151,1436,175,1818]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A. Holotype of Pogostemon petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); B. Isotype of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K); C. Leaves of P. petelotii (Pételot 1300, P); D. Leaves of P. cruciatus (Wallich 1541, K). Scale bars: C, D = 1 cm. A and C reproduced with permisson by the Muséum National d'Histoire Naturelle (MNHN), Paris; B and D with permission by Herbarium of the Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew (K))" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071557/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Fig. 1 D</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="68E4C0FE0D14FFD2A0D0F9C9DDECA1DC" authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Bentham" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[1268,1408,1657,1682]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cruciatus">
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A0D0F9C9DDECA1DC" box="[1268,1408,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">P. cruciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in 
<collectingCountry id="D7F3FBED0D14FFD2A51DF910D914A1F4" box="[313,376,1696,1722]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="D7F3FBED0D14FFD2A5A0F910D9A1A1F4" box="[388,461,1696,1722]" name="Nepal" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="D7F3FBED0D14FFD2A5FDF910DA21A1F4" box="[473,589,1696,1722]" name="Myanmar" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="D7F3FBED0D14FFD2A67CF910DACDA1F4" box="[600,673,1696,1722]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="D7F3FBED0D14FFD2A689F910DB74A1F4" box="[685,792,1696,1722]" name="Thailand" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="D7F3FBED0D14FFD2A700F910DBE6A1F4" box="[804,906,1696,1722]" name="Vietnam" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="D7F3FBED0D14FFD2A7B1F910DBA2A1F4" box="[917,974,1696,1722]" name="Laos" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Laos</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="D7F3FBED0D14FFD2A023F910DCEFA1F4" box="[1031,1155,1696,1722]" name="Cambodia" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Cambodia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AF5BBB7D0D14FFD2A4E2F976DD00A0EC" blockId="1.[151,1436,845,1954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">
Trichomes are widely used in taxomomic studies in the family 
<taxonomicName id="68E4C0FE0D14FFD2A79FF976DC56A1AE" authorityName=", Suddee &amp; Paton" authorityYear="2006" box="[955,1082,1734,1760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Lamiaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CB75C68C0D14FFD2A06FF976DC9CA1AE" author="Cantino, P. D." box="[1099,1264,1734,1760]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" pagination="323 - 370" refId="ref2414" refString="Cantino, P. D. (1990) The phylogenetics significance of stomata and trichomes in the Labiatae and Verbenaceae. Journal of the Arnold Arboretum 71: 323 - 370." type="journal article" year="1990">Cantino 1990</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CB75C68C0D14FFD2A0DBF976D8B8A049" author="Gairola, S. &amp; Naidoo, Y. &amp; Bhatt, A. &amp; Nicholas, A." pageId="1" pageNumber="39" pagination="325 - 330" refId="ref2547" refString="Gairola, S., Naidoo, Y., Bhatt, A. &amp; Nicholas, A. (2009) An investigation of the foliar trichomes of Tetradenia riparia (Hochst.) Codd (Lamiaceae): An important medicinal plant of Southern Africa. Flora 204: 325 - 330. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. flora. 2008.04.002" type="journal article" year="2009">
Gairola 
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A17BF977DDF9A1AE" box="[1375,1429,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CB75C68C0D14FFD2A4C4F95DD9C0A049" author="Xiang, C. L. &amp; Dong, Z. H. &amp; Peng, H. &amp; Liu, Z. W." box="[224,428,1773,1799]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" pagination="434 - 441" refId="ref3471" refString="Xiang, C. L., Dong, Z. H., Peng, H. &amp; Liu, Z. W. (2010) Trichome micromorphology of the East Asiatic genus Chelonopsis (Lamiaceae) and its systematic implications. Flora 205: 434 - 441. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. flora. 2009.12.007" type="journal article" year="2010">
Xiang 
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A50AF95DD90CA048" box="[302,352,1773,1798]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CB75C68C0D14FFD2A59CF95DDA08A049" author="Hu, G. X. &amp; Balangcod, T. D. &amp; Xiang, C. L." box="[440,612,1773,1799]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" pagination="867 - 874" refId="ref2765" refString="Hu, G. X., Balangcod, T. D. &amp; Xiang, C. L. (2012) Trichome micromorphology of the Chinese-Himalayan genus Colquhounia (Lamiaceae), with emphasis on taxonomic implications. Biologia, Section Botany 67: 867 - 874. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2478 / s 11756 - 012 - 0076 - z" type="journal article" year="2012">
Hu 
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A5C7F95DDA79A048" box="[483,533,1773,1798]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="68E4C0FE0D14FFD2A6B1F95DDB4AA048" authorityName="Desfontaines" authorityYear="1815" box="[661,806,1773,1798]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A6B1F95DDB4AA048" box="[661,806,1773,1798]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Pogostemon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, most species have multi-cellular, simple hairs except for two species that have unicellular hairs (
<bibRefCitation id="CB75C68C0D14FFD2A6B6F8A4DBD0A060" author="Bhatti, G. R. &amp; Ingrouille, M." box="[658,956,1812,1838]" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" pagination="77 - 147" refId="ref2327" refString="Bhatti, G. R. &amp; Ingrouille, M. (1997) Systematics of Pogostemon (Labiatae). Bulletin of the Natural History Museum, Botany Series 27: 77 - 147." type="book chapter" year="1997">Bhatti &amp; Ingrouille 1997</bibRefCitation>
). We observed the trichome morphology of leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="68E4C0FE0D14FFD2A501F88BD9CEA01A" authorityName="Doan ex Gang Yao, Y. F. Deng &amp; X. J. Ge" authorityYear="2013" box="[293,418,1851,1876]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petelotii">
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A501F88BD9CEA01A" box="[293,418,1851,1876]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">P. petelotii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="68E4C0FE0D14FFD2A5FEF88BDA0BA01A" authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Bentham" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[474,615,1851,1876]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cruciatus">
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A5FEF88BDA0BA01A" box="[474,615,1851,1876]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">P.cruciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under scanning electron microscopy and light microscopy. The results showed that 
<taxonomicName id="68E4C0FE0D14FFD2A50EF8D1D9CBA034" authorityName="Doan ex Gang Yao, Y. F. Deng &amp; X. J. Ge" authorityYear="2013" box="[298,423,1889,1914]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="petelotii">
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A50EF8D1D9CBA034" box="[298,423,1889,1914]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">P. petelotii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has unicellular hairs (
<figureCitation id="37DFA7F80D14FFD2A68DF8D1DB6AA035" box="[681,774,1889,1915]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,245,1931,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,462,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-196@4.[151,1436,462,1915]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Trichome morphology of leaves under scanning electron microscope and light microscope. Pogostemon cruciatus (G. Forrest 25140, IBSC): A. Trichome on the upper surface; C. Trichome on the lower surface; E. 2–3-cellular trichome. P. petelotii (T. Sörensen et al. 6313, KUN): B. Trichome on the upper surface; D. Trichome on lower surface; F. unicellular trichome. Scale bars: E–F = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071563/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Fig. 3 F</figureCitation>
) more densely covered on the leaf surfaces (
<figureCitation id="37DFA7F80D14FFD2A12AF8D1DDE2A035" box="[1294,1422,1889,1915]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,245,1931,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,462,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-196@4.[151,1436,462,1915]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Trichome morphology of leaves under scanning electron microscope and light microscope. Pogostemon cruciatus (G. Forrest 25140, IBSC): A. Trichome on the upper surface; C. Trichome on the lower surface; E. 2–3-cellular trichome. P. petelotii (T. Sörensen et al. 6313, KUN): B. Trichome on the upper surface; D. Trichome on lower surface; F. unicellular trichome. Scale bars: E–F = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071563/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Fig 3 B, D</figureCitation>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="68E4C0FE0D14FFD2A4ECF838D93AA0EF" authorityName="Kuntze" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Bentham" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[200,342,1928,1953]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cruciatus">
<emphasis id="9D90676F0D14FFD2A4ECF838D93AA0EF" box="[200,342,1928,1953]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">P.cruciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 2–3-cellular hairs (
<figureCitation id="37DFA7F80D14FFD2A642F838DAA9A0EC" box="[614,709,1928,1954]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,245,1931,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,462,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-196@4.[151,1436,462,1915]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Trichome morphology of leaves under scanning electron microscope and light microscope. Pogostemon cruciatus (G. Forrest 25140, IBSC): A. Trichome on the upper surface; C. Trichome on the lower surface; E. 2–3-cellular trichome. P. petelotii (T. Sörensen et al. 6313, KUN): B. Trichome on the upper surface; D. Trichome on lower surface; F. unicellular trichome. Scale bars: E–F = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071563/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Fig. 3 E</figureCitation>
) more sparsely covered on the leaf surfaces (
<figureCitation id="37DFA7F80D14FFD2A0F3F838DD33A0EC" box="[1239,1375,1928,1954]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,245,1931,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,462,1914]" captionTargetId="figure-196@4.[151,1436,462,1915]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Trichome morphology of leaves under scanning electron microscope and light microscope. Pogostemon cruciatus (G. Forrest 25140, IBSC): A. Trichome on the upper surface; C. Trichome on the lower surface; E. 2–3-cellular trichome. P. petelotii (T. Sörensen et al. 6313, KUN): B. Trichome on the upper surface; D. Trichome on lower surface; F. unicellular trichome. Scale bars: E–F = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5071563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5071563/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="39">Fig. 3 A, C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
